synopsis: Eskimo's Go Wild In San Diego follows a group of five young Eskimos who, want to escape their Alaskan communities, they head to San Diego with very little money hoping to finds jobs, here they experience life beyond their Illuvut for the very first time. When Q, Tamara, Mary, Frank and Nuala land in San Diego, they quickly discover that the 'Lower 48' is drastically different to Alaska. They buy swimming costumes for the first time in there lives so they can enjoy swimming and surfing like the locals. When they get talking to the local people on the beach they assume they all live in igloos and when they tell them there favourite food is seal the locals are horrified. They all have there ups and downs and miss home a lot there parents really relay a lot on these kids to help to pay towards day to day living back in Alaska.
